    <h1>ALVAO WebApp</h1>
    <p>
        <a href="../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp">ALVAO WebApp</a> is a web application for working with <a href="../alvao-service-desk">ALVAO Service Desk</a> and <a href="../alvao-asset-management">ALVAO Asset Management</a>.
    </p>

    <p>To access the application, use a <a href="implementation/requirements">supported</a> web browser. Your system administrator will provide you with the address of the application.</p>
    <p>Depending on your system settings, you will usually need to <a href="../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp/login">login</a> with your username and password.</p>

    <p>Within the ALVAO Asset Management product, the ALVAO WebApp serves:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>common users - to check <a href="../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp/search/persons/person">trusted assets</a>, to electronically sign <a href="../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp/search/persons/person">documents</a>, to perform <a href="../modules/alvao-inventory-audits/web-asset-check">web inventory</a>.</li>
        <li>asset managers - to search and perform basic asset operations. Advanced features are only available in the <a href="../alvao-asset-management" translate="no">ALVAO Asset Management Console</a>.</li>
    </ul>

</asp:Content>
